Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.47,0:02:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Full moon. Lock up tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.48,0:02:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Better the wolf takes the pig than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.52,0:02:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We lived on the edge of a dark forest.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.52,0:02:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Few knew our village by name...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.76,0:02:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...but many had heard of the terrible{\i}\N{\i1}things that happened there.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.29,0:02:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My mother always told me{\i},\N{\i1}"Don't talk to strangers.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.60,0:02:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go get water and come straight home."{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.64,0:02:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I tried to be a good girl{\i}\N{\i1}and do what she said.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.68,0:02:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.45,0:02:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Believe me, I tried.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.78,0:02:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.09,0:02:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.26,0:03:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.54,0:03:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, snow white fur.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.31,0:03:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you a pair of hunting boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.82,0:03:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do it, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.36,0:03:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You do it.\N- No, you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.03,0:03:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:04:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know good girls aren't supposed{\i}\N{\i1}to hunt rabbits or go into the woods alone.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.22,0:04:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But since we were kids, he always had a{\i}\N{\i1}way of making me wanna break the rules.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.30,0:04:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter! Trees'll still be there after we eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Give me that.\N- What will you give me for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.29,0:05:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- They didn't tell you?\N- Tell me what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've arranged for you to marry\NHenry Lazar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.74,0:05:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, my mother finally got\Nwhat she wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.61,0:05:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.71,0:05:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Henry gets what he's always wanted.\NYou.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.88,0:05:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.32,0:05:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to marry him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.09,0:05:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.29,0:05:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.93,0:05:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- How?\N- Run away with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.30,0:05:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where would we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.57,0:05:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anywhere you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.64,0:05:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.14,0:06:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The city.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.57,0:06:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You afraid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.01,0:06:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- No.\N- Oh, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.62,0:06:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd leave your home?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.26,0:06:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.93,0:06:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your whole life?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.80,0:06:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would do anything to be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.67,0:06:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.74,0:06:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, did you?\N- Ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.74,0:06:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.65,0:06:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be half a day's ride before\Nanyone knows we're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.15,0:06:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll race you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.83,0:07:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.87,0:07:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way! Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.56,0:07:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It killed again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.52,0:07:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we've kept the peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.23,0:07:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the wolf has broken it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.16,0:07:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.30,0:07:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.30,0:07:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.41,0:07:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.09,0:08:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucie!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.63,0:08:11.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucie!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.28,0:08:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Claude.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.65,0:09:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Madame Lazar, please come in.\N- Suzette.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.26,0:09:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm sorry for your loss.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.36,0:09:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.50,0:09:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hello, Henry.\N- Ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.94,0:09:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucie was a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.68,0:09:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's your fianc{\i1}é{\i} now.\NHe's come to offer his condolences.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.58,0:09:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- But I barely know him.\N- You'll get to know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.49,0:09:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now go down there. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.63,0:09:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cesaire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.77,0:09:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come with us to the tavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.10,0:09:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let the women grieve in their own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.22,0:10:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- L... I... I want to go.\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't love your father\Nwhen we were first married.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.70,0:10:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in love with another man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.14,0:10:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I came to love your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.01,0:10:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he gave me\Ntwo beautiful daughters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.39,0:10:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should count our blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.19,0:10:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.39,0:10:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been almost 20 years since\Nthe wolf has taken a human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.99,0:10:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.56,0:10:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because we sacrifice\Nour best livestock every full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.07,0:10:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We kept our end of the bargain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.74,0:11:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- So now we kill it.\N- Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.01,0:11:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's kill that thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.98,0:11:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.25,0:11:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've summoned Father Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.08,0:11:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Father Solomon?\N- Ha-ha-ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.98,0:11:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has destroyed werewolves and witches\Nin cities throughout the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.79,0:11:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He will rid us of this beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.02,0:11:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.09,0:11:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll rob us of our vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.36,0:11:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why she was outside\Non a wolf night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.10,0:11:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she snuck out to meet a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.43,0:11:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lucie never even\Nthought about boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.57,0:11:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was certainly taken\Nwith my grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.91,0:11:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She used to come by and follow him\Nabout like a puppy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.45,0:11:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She found out that night that Henry\Nwas engaged to her sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.65,0:11:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must have been heartbroken.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.26,0:11:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she chose to die\Nrather than live without him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.26,0:11:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.83,0:11:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prudence!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.13,0:11:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unspeakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.76,0:12:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She never even told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.30,0:12:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.04,0:12:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Henry always had his eye on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.94,0:12:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the pretty one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.29,0:12:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm paying my respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.63,0:12:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know exactly why you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.99,0:12:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already lost one daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.83,0:12:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie's all I have left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.43,0:12:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have nothing to offer her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.63,0:12:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a trade. The same one\Nas your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.87,0:12:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what a woodcutter earns.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.34,0:12:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Henry's her only hope for a better life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.85,0:12:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you love her...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.92,0:12:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you'll let her go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.84,0:13:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've all seen the bones on the trail\Nto Mount Grimmoor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.74,0:13:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's where the wolf makes its lair.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.01,0:13:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We know the weaknesses of the werewolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.08,0:13:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't come out in daylight.\NIt can't step onto holy ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.71,0:13:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- And there's silver.\N- That'll kill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.25,0:13:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silver!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.55,0:13:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Father Auguste is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.99,0:13:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.19,0:13:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.49,0:13:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, my son...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.50,0:13:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you should find your courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to hunt the wolf?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.70,0:13:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hunt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.17,0:13:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's kill it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.47,0:13:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's kill the beast!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.31,0:13:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's kill it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.68,0:13:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.66,0:14:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you with me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.40,0:14:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.87,0:14:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.17,0:14:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my sister. I can't lose you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.31,0:14:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do this anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.28,0:14:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to go through with it.\NYou have to marry Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.05,0:14:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know I don't want Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.62,0:14:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make this something it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.82,0:14:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, we had our fun.\NThat's all it ever was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.96,0:14:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.97,0:14:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made something for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.02,0:15:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was gonna wait until our wedding,\Nbut, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.52,0:15:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.72,0:15:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will be happy again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.46,0:15:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.80,0:15:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.24,0:15:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.87,0:15:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We should wait for Father Solomon.\N- No!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.88,0:15:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be here tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.41,0:15:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We're gonna kill the wolf.\N- We can take care of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.45,0:15:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it? Nobody else?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.45,0:15:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! Go home to your mama's, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.78,0:16:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adrian. Thank you for standing up for\NLucie. That was no small thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.28,0:16:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be family soon.\NYou'd have done the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.21,0:16:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Promise me you'll be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.18,0:16:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.75,0:16:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf doesn't want me. I'm all gristle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.76,0:16:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean it, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.53,0:16:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promise, Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.44,0:17:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.84,0:17:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.61,0:17:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darling. Darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.45,0:17:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.48,0:17:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.26,0:17:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many things\Nshe didn't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.03,0:17:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm her sister. I should've known.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.83,0:17:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was her choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.47,0:17:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We all have secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.28,0:17:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember what my grandma\Nused to say:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.15,0:17:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- "All sorrows are less with bread."\N- "Less with bread."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.87,0:18:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. Try this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.39,0:18:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.59,0:18:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was making it for your wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.94,0:18:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like it's my wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.28,0:18:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.98,0:18:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm being sold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.19,0:19:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.71,0:19:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better watch yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a fork.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's split up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.49,0:20:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another fork.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.83,0:20:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take the steep one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.50,0:20:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. We should stay together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.60,0:21:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.58,0:21:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.85,0:21:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Grandmother told us{\i}\N{\i1}that the wolf used to kill entire families...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.78,0:21:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...snatching children from their beds.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.72,0:21:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Those stories never seemed real to me.{\i}\N{\i1}Until now.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.65,0:22:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ripped the thing out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.77,0:22:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claude.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.04,0:23:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.11,0:23:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For his sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.01,0:23:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.68,0:23:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poor Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.39,0:23:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.73,0:23:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father was a brave man.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.83,0:23:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I was close enough to smell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.34,0:23:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I was afraid. And I hid from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.21,0:23:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.21,0:23:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should've saved him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.59,0:24:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Henry...\N- Just leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.86,0:24:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you to see me like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.20,0:24:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Henry's father, wasn't it?\NThe man you loved?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.30,0:24:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucie was in love with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.37,0:24:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was a year older than me.\NShe could've married him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.47,0:24:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you insist it was me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.98,0:25:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you know the answer to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.71,0:25:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.85,0:25:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucie was Henry's half-sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.59,0:25:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adrian was her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.03,0:25:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does Papa know about Lucie?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.03,0:25:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. And you have to promise me\Nthat you'll never tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.91,0:25:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.58,0:25:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.04,0:26:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claude.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.87,0:26:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Presenting His Eminence...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.80,0:26:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.81,0:26:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.25,0:26:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please don't cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.08,0:26:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see? You see all these children?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.42,0:26:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see how scared they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.92,0:26:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a big, bad wolf.\NSomeone has to stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.90,0:27:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the beast that killed our mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.20,0:27:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may very well be.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.94,0:27:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on. I'll join you soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.30,0:27:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.94,0:27:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.43,0:27:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is indeed an honor, Your Eminence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.16,0:27:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.\NYou've arrived just in time for our festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.80,0:27:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see,\Nthe werewolf has been dealt with.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.71,0:27:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not a werewolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.45,0:27:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No disrespect...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.89,0:28:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but we have been living\Nwith this beast for two generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.86,0:28:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We know what we're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.59,0:28:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, no disrespect...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.03,0:28:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but you have no idea\Nwhat you are dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.67,0:28:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was like you once.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.10,0:28:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My wife's name was Penelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.34,0:28:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She gave me two beautiful daughters.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.48,0:28:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were a very happy family.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.25,0:28:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We lived in a village like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.05,0:28:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And like Daggerhorn...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.72,0:28:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...ours was plagued by a werewolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.16,0:28:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One full moon,\Nmy friends and I got drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.06,0:28:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We decided to hunt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.90,0:28:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It never occurred to us that we might\Nactually find it, but find it we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.44,0:28:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It ripped...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.24,0:28:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...my best friend in half.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.85,0:28:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.68,0:29:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then it was on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.28,0:29:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hacked and hacked at it with my axe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.59,0:29:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.99,0:29:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.26,0:29:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had cut off one of its front paws.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.67,0:29:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it might make a clever\Nsouvenir, and so I took it home.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.83,0:29:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there I found my wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.41,0:29:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...with a bloody rag\Nwrapped around her wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.28,0:29:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when I opened my sack...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.08,0:29:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the werewolf's paw...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.91,0:29:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.82,0:29:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was in its place.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.43,0:29:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told my girls\Nthe werewolf killed their mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.80,0:29:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.50,0:29:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.84,0:30:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a werewolf dies,\Nit returns to its human form.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.14,0:30:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is just a common gray wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.65,0:30:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your werewolf...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.79,0:30:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is still very much alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.14,0:30:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is one of only three silver\Nswords blessed by the Holy See.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.92,0:30:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May I touch?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.48,0:30:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.32,0:30:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a very dangerous time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.29,0:30:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You all know\Nwhat the Blood Moon means.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.93,0:30:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They have no idea what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.68,0:31:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The orrery.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.15,0:31:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The red planet converges with the moon\Nonce every 13 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.99,0:31:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only time\Na new werewolf can be created.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.13,0:31:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During the week of the Blood Moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.17,0:31:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the werewolf may pass his curse on\Nwith a single bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.34,0:31:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During a normal full moon,\Na wolf bite will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.28,0:31:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But during a Blood Moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.85,0:31:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...your very souls are in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.35,0:31:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until the Blood Moon wanes in three days...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.46,0:31:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you will never truly be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.12,0:31:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're safe now.\NI killed the wolf in its lair.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.33,0:32:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cave at Mount Grimmoor.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.23,0:32:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have been deceived\Nby this beast from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.87,0:32:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It made you think\Nit lived on Grimmoor...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.90,0:32:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so that you would not look for it\Nin the most obvious place.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.97,0:32:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf lives here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.68,0:32:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this village.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.54,0:32:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Among you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.98,0:32:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real killer could be your neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.68,0:32:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What?\N- Your best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.82,0:32:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.20,0:32:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Barricade the village.\N- You can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.34,0:32:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Post men at every gate!\NNo one leaves until we kill the wolf!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.84,0:32:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- As you wish.\N- The wolf is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.68,0:32:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight we celebrate!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.78,0:32:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.10,0:33:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead. Celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.60,0:33:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll see who is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.85,0:33:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf is dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.02,0:33:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.67,0:33:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll huff, and I'll puff...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.51,0:33:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and I'll blow your house down!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.80,0:34:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Laugh at the little man!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.12,0:34:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie, come dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.40,0:34:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll huff...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.70,0:34:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll puff...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.03,0:34:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and I'll blow your house down.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.34,0:34:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.22,0:35:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just flick this off.\NI'll be fit to see the pope.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.42,0:35:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.59,0:35:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're my good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.06,0:35:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.17,0:35:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know. Just go home now, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.03,0:35:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tricked you. Ha-ha-ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.16,0:35:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.53,0:35:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you learn that?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.03,0:36:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claude.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.57,0:36:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claude, come back to the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.19,0:36:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Rose has a new conquest.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.71,0:36:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Prudence.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.03,0:37:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You left us!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.83,0:37:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take it easy, friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.04,0:37:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said we should stick together and you\Nleft us, and my father is dead because of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.24,0:37:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.71,0:37:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your hands off her\Nor I'll cut them off!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.01,0:37:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.21,0:38:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.87,0:38:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter with you?\NWhat do I have to do to make you stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.41,0:38:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love you, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.25,0:38:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing with Rose?\NYou don't even like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.52,0:38:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have to like her\Nto get what I want from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.12,0:38:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a terrible liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.12,0:38:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you feel like I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.46,0:38:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're burning inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.40,0:38:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never be able to give you\Nanything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.83,0:38:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think I care about Henry's money?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.53,0:38:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a future with him.\NI'm not gonna let you ruin that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.64,0:38:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did my mother get to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.34,0:38:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie, I'm wrong for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.08,0:39:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.00,0:39:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could eat you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.95,0:40:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want me?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.16,0:40:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.66,0:40:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, give us a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.34,0:40:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only life I want is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.72,0:41:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So where did you disappear to?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.59,0:41:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know all that soft hay\Nin the granary?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.28,0:41:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Run!\N- Get to the church!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.92,0:41:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Peter!\N- Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.62,0:41:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claude!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.39,0:42:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will die now, beast!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.90,0:42:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf can't cross onto holy ground!\NGet to the church!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.51,0:42:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The church!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.78,0:42:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claude!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.32,0:42:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Rope it!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.56,0:42:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold him!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.86,0:42:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claude!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.11,0:42:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- It's strong.\N- God is stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.01,0:42:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God is stronger!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.47,0:43:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I warned you!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.71,0:43:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I warned you!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.08,0:43:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your werewolf is still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.65,0:43:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.16,0:43:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.16,0:43:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.50,0:43:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.17,0:44:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't escape from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.77,0:44:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God. You can speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.17,0:44:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.58,0:44:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You understand me.\NThat's all that matters, Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.05,0:44:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.55,0:44:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.56,0:44:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Human eyes, dark brown.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.23,0:44:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you well.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.63,0:44:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You dream of leaving this village.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.93,0:44:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let me take you away.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.10,0:44:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.97,0:45:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm nothing like you.\NYou're a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.51,0:45:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a killer too, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.71,0:45:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the rabbit, Valerie?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.62,0:45:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.29,0:45:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know. So come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.12,0:45:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.32,0:45:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the streets will run red\Nwith blood. Starting with hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.10,0:45:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.23,0:45:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Solomon will stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.00,0:45:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Solomon will die like the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.97,0:45:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming back for you\Nbefore the Blood Moon wanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.24,0:45:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There! Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.76,0:45:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talked to the wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.36,0:45:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it talked to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.00,0:45:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it growled.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.43,0:46:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you heard it talk to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.40,0:46:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll call me a witch.\NDon't tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.71,0:46:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.44,0:46:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Get inside onto holy ground.\N- Wait, I have to find my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.51,0:46:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- And my family.\N- No one leaves until sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.38,0:46:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Go.\N- For your own safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.57,0:46:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were wrong to have doubted you,\NFather.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.28,0:46:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen a beast as strong as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.95,0:46:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A creature this powerful must come\Nfrom a long uninterrupted bloodline.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.26,0:46:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each generation\Nmore potent than the one before.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.36,0:47:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must find it in its human form.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.90,0:47:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how? It could be any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.40,0:47:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't survived this long\Nby being obvious. Look everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.87,0:47:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look for the signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.41,0:47:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.11,0:47:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Witchcraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.25,0:47:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The black arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.22,0:47:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Abnormal behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.42,0:47:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange smells.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.06,0:47:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your homes will be searched.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.29,0:47:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your secrets brought to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.76,0:47:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you are innocent,\Nyou have nothing to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.60,0:47:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you are guilty...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.37,0:47:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I swear by Almighty God...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.97,0:47:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.01,0:47:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.98,0:47:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring me water!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.58,0:47:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.27,0:48:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a Blood Moon. So he must...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.87,0:48:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.76,0:48:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man bitten...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.43,0:48:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is a man cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.23,0:49:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie, open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.24,0:49:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all in danger.\NSo we've gotta leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.98,0:49:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come away with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.98,0:49:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come away with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.02,0:49:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come away with me.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.12,0:49:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get your things. We have to leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.10,0:49:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go with you, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.63,0:49:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.24,0:49:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.96,0:50:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.46,0:50:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's going to be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.17,0:50:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf just scratched her.\NThat's not a bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.84,0:50:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lift her head, Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.24,0:50:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. Drink this, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.31,0:50:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll help you sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.13,0:50:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.91,0:51:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, darling?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.08,0:51:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.28,0:51:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.22,0:51:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It talked to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.19,0:51:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you understood it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.72,0:51:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As clearly as I understand you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.10,0:51:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you told anyone else about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.20,0:51:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only Roxanne knows,\Nbut she won't tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.87,0:51:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She won't even talk to me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.24,0:51:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It chose not to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.88,0:51:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it wants me alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.13,0:52:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- No.\N- Bring me another bandage.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.13,0:52:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.87,0:52:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to get clean water.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.65,0:52:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has Claude come home?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.58,0:52:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.42,0:52:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you go, back inside. Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.39,0:52:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to let us in.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.10,0:52:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw you with Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.90,0:52:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you don't want me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.21,0:52:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna force you to marry me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.02,0:52:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna break off the engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.67,0:53:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.08,0:53:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.38,0:53:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Solomon!\NWe found someone hiding!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.65,0:53:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.19,0:53:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.83,0:53:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- It's my brother! Don't touch him!\N- Get him down!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.43,0:53:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Interrogate him!\N- He's not the wolf!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.47,0:53:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at him!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.10,0:53:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His speech is twisted.\NHe communes with demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.47,0:53:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get him down! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.41,0:53:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't done anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.68,0:54:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is proof\Nthat he studies the black arts!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.72,0:54:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a conjurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.92,0:54:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I know him.\N- Better than I knew my own wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.39,0:54:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You never know\Nwhat someone is capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.12,0:54:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get him down! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.22,0:54:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me the name of the wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.56,0:54:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.53,0:54:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me the name!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.35,0:55:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Romans invented this.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.85,0:55:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An ingenious system\Nfor extracting the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.99,0:55:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can he give you a name?\NThe boy can barely speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.79,0:55:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to how he sings\Nof his love of Satan.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.73,0:55:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We do this for the greater good.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.64,0:55:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the good in this?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.08,0:55:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed my wife to protect my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.45,0:55:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our methods of pleasing God\Nare sometimes flawed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.22,0:55:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had best develop a stomach for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.28,0:56:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She says it's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.19,0:56:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come to bargain\Nfor the release of my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.13,0:56:30.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silver fingernails.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.56,0:56:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To kill a werewolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.94,0:56:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.37,0:56:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, I have more than money to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.03,0:57:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.54,0:57:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough. Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.00,0:57:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, please. I have something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.84,0:57:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spare my brother\Nand I'll give you the name of a witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.92,0:57:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.59,0:57:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is worth something.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.43,0:57:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell them what you told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.67,0:57:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can climb the tallest trees.\NShe can run faster than all the girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.14,0:57:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She wears a red cloak.\NThe devil's color.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.31,0:57:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nonsense. I made that cloak.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.85,0:57:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence! Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.02,0:57:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she can talk to werewolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.35,0:58:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen it. With my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.90,0:58:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you deny it?\N- No, I don't deny it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.07,0:58:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what was the nature\Nof this conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.98,0:58:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It promised to leave Daggerhorn\Nin peace as long as I go with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.28,0:58:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf is someone in this village\Nwho wants you, Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.89,0:58:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know who it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.76,0:58:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd think very hard if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.50,0:58:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.10,0:58:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.64,0:58:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.75,0:59:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wants her, not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.52,0:59:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to save yourselves,\Nsimply give it what it wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.49,0:59:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't give her to the wolf.\NThat's human sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.39,0:59:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've all made sacrifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.49,0:59:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The trial is over.\NGo back to your homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.70,0:59:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said go home. All of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.10,0:59:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I thought you cared about her.\N- I do care.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.67,0:59:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do care.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.65,0:59:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm trying to be smart about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.28,0:59:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to the granary.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.45,0:59:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna try and rescue her?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.06,0:59:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well, I'll help.\N- I'm not that desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.90,0:59:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really? Then what's your plan, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.63,0:59:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, you don't have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.90,1:00:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, you've seen those locks.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.84,1:00:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a shop and I've got tools.\NYou need me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.78,1:00:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.85,1:00:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're the wolf,\NI'm gonna chop your head off.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.59,1:00:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will do the same to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.82,1:00:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.49,1:00:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go home!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.40,1:00:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's my brother? Father Solomon\Ntold me you'd release him.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.84,1:00:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.95,1:01:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.22,1:01:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bread. Blanket.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.62,1:01:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need anything else?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.26,1:01:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not want you to use that knife.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.30,1:01:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We have to find the wolf.\N- By sundown?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.17,1:01:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, the wolf wants you.\NBut first it killed your sister.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.17,1:01:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I didn't know it,\Nbut Lucie was in love with Henry.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.28,1:01:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when she found out\Nabout my engagement...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.95,1:01:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...she gave herself to the wolf.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.42,1:01:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Lucie wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.32,1:02:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Your time is up.\N- But she might have responded to Henry.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.70,1:02:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please see that she gets that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.14,1:02:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oaf.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.46,1:02:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cesaire.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.29,1:02:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna save your daughter.\NAnd then I intend to marry her.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.93,1:02:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like your blessing in this,\Nbut I can live without it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.94,1:02:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can I do?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.22,1:03:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're closed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.88,1:03:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.72,1:03:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Henry.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.69,1:03:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I brought you some biscuits.\N- Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.53,1:03:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanna thank you\Nfor speaking up this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.63,1:03:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, try some.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.90,1:03:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.37,1:03:24.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was very brave of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.18,1:03:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said what I felt.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.78,1:03:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.91,1:03:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I want you to know you're under no\Nobligation to stand up for Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.69,1:03:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're no longer engaged to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.45,1:03:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's in love with someone else.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.29,1:03:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't mean\NI've stopped caring about her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.06,1:03:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I imagine that's just how\NLucie felt about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.06,1:03:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had a crush on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.66,1:03:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, more than a crush. I think she would\Nhave done absolutely anything for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.37,1:03:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even agree to meet you on a wolf night\Nif you asked her to.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.38,1:04:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.29,1:04:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I'm the wolf?\NAre you accusing me of murder?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.89,1:04:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not accusing you of anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.43,1:04:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to find out the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.90,1:04:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.44,1:04:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My God, it's you.\NI can smell it on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.34,1:04:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh. What can you smell on me?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.41,1:04:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The night my father died, I could smell\Nthe wolf. It was like a deep musk.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.31,1:04:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I can smell it all over you right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.25,1:04:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you do out there in that cabin\Nall by yourself in the middle of the night?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.92,1:04:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the night that Lucie died?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.26,1:04:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know, do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.20,1:04:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what you're doing. And I'm not\Ngonna let you turn this on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.69,1:05:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.59,1:05:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're coming with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.11,1:06:11.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I haven't done anything.\N- Just a precaution.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.58,1:06:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Solomon doesn't want\Nany trouble from the witch's family.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.75,1:06:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to put on your harlot's robe.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.08,1:06:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.28,1:06:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did my best to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.89,1:06:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and Lucie.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.29,1:06:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Papa.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.69,1:07:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You taught us to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.11,1:07:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Father Solomon had designed{\i}\N{\i1}the mask for public disgrace.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.55,1:07:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And even my friends stared, judging me.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.15,1:07:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.59,1:07:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What if they were right?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.52,1:07:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Maybe the wolf knew something I didn't.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.56,1:07:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Maybe there was something{\i}\N{\i1}dark inside of me.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.33,1:07:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should all go home!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.94,1:07:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry, Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.61,1:07:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean for this to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.05,1:07:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bless you, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.99,1:08:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prudence.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.32,1:08:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.93,1:08:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roxanne wanted me\Nto tell you how sorry she is.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.83,1:08:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- She said those things to save her brother.\N- I know. Tell her that I forgive her.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.47,1:08:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.67,1:08:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wanted to say...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.84,1:08:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.21,1:08:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you don't have to say anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.91,1:08:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.91,1:08:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to know that...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.32,1:08:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you may have fooled Roxanne...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.19,1:08:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but you don't fool me.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.16,1:08:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.99,1:08:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were always too good.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.46,1:08:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too pretty.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.70,1:08:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.23,1:08:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You tricked us.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.24,1:08:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you're gonna get what you deserve.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.87,1:09:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prudence, I think you should go.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.78,1:09:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.18,1:09:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be long now.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.65,1:09:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf is coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.96,1:09:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wolf lives here.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.06,1:09:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your neighbor. Your best friend.{\i}\N{\i1}Even your wife.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.80,1:09:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the pretty one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.23,1:09:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I could eat you up.\N- You will be happy again.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.70,1:09:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Human eyes, dark brown.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.47,1:09:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know you well.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.25,1:09:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know how you kill a tiger,\NFather Auguste?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.66,1:09:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You tie out your best goat...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.47,1:09:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.79,1:10:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.46,1:11:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Put it out!\N- Unh.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.50,1:11:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.09,1:11:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna get you out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.93,1:11:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too much!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.79,1:12:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.55,1:12:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There! He's taken the bait! Fire!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.22,1:12:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, that's not the wolf!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.72,1:12:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's aiding a witch!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.52,1:12:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Fire!\N- No!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.52,1:12:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.43,1:12:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.95,1:13:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one started the fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.45,1:13:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lock him up. In the elephant!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.45,1:13:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Go!\N- Move it!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.66,1:13:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The witch has escaped!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.71,1:13:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get over here! Find the witch!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.62,1:13:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Peter's meeting us\Nwith the horses.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.53,1:13:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.60,1:13:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.54,1:13:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Peter?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.77,1:13:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.88,1:14:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.75,1:14:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he doesn't show...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.02,1:14:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm gonna take you away.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.58,1:14:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let me take you away.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.59,1:14:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I'm the wolf?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.93,1:14:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find the witch!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.73,1:14:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.20,1:14:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.64,1:14:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.91,1:14:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should go to the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.25,1:14:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolf can't cross onto holy ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.88,1:14:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some with me! This way! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.76,1:14:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard something over there.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.40,1:14:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're in here! After them!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.04,1:15:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Valerie.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.92,1:15:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Henry. Henry.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.39,1:15:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go. Valerie, go!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.59,1:15:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'm not leaving you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.30,1:15:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We claim sanctuary.\N- You are not on holy ground yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.97,1:15:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- This...\N- Unh.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.91,1:15:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...belongs to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.60,1:16:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want her alive?!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.53,1:16:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill it!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.62,1:16:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.15,1:16:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Step across the gate,\Nor I'll destroy this village.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.86,1:16:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me before the sun rises.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.56,1:16:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make your decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.27,1:16:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you destroy my home.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.41,1:16:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'll go with you.\N- Don't! Valerie. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.21,1:16:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you promise to leave them alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.31,1:16:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I won't let you\Nsacrifice yourself for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.02,1:16:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Nor will I.\N- Nor will I.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.72,1:16:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I stand by Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.09,1:17:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't hide from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.77,1:17:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Aah!\N- The witch will still burn!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.32,1:17:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under the Blood Moon...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.99,1:17:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a man bitten is a man cursed.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.52,1:17:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My children will be orphaned.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.63,1:17:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.13,1:17:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...had children too.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.47,1:17:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I meant only to serve.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.47,1:17:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To protect us from darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.86,1:18:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under the Blood Moon...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.23,1:18:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a man bitten is a man cursed.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.25,1:18:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Peter?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.72,1:18:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Peter?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.45,1:19:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.39,1:19:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What big eyes you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.09,1:19:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The better to see you with, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.74,1:19:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandmother, what big ears you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.77,1:19:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The better to hear you with, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.18,1:19:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What big teeth you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.88,1:19:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The better to eat you with, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.57,1:20:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie. What are you doing out of bed?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.38,1:20:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so worried.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.05,1:20:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks much better.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.16,1:20:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.43,1:20:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Grandmother's.\NI think she's in danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.47,1:21:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going after the wolf\Nbefore the storm can cover its tracks.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.61,1:21:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be human again\Nand we can finally kill it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.11,1:21:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I have...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.35,1:21:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.35,1:21:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter is still missing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.92,1:21:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do what I have to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.86,1:21:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please be careful.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.54,1:22:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.98,1:22:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank God you're all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.99,1:22:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.26,1:22:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was trapped in that brazen beast all night.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.09,1:22:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally broke out.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.96,1:22:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come near me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.43,1:22:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie, what?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.80,1:22:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't believe me?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.53,1:22:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.54,1:22:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.34,1:22:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.31,1:23:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandmother!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.78,1:23:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandmother, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.99,1:23:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.29,1:23:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ah!\N- I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.53,1:23:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just woke up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.63,1:23:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's some soup if you're hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.17,1:23:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I think the wolf is out there.\N- It's all right, darling. We're safe in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.01,1:24:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat up. Remember:
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.38,1:24:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- "All sorrows are less with bread."\N- "Less with bread."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.98,1:24:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.15,1:24:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat up, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.69,1:24:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.90,1:24:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.77,1:24:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.04,1:24:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.55,1:24:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She finally realized what I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.13,1:24:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you do this?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.16,1:24:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.57,1:24:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.64,1:25:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.01,1:25:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been so disrespected.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.48,1:25:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've settled for far less than I deserve.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.45,1:25:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I decided I'd leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.95,1:25:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the city.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.69,1:25:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For richer hunting grounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.53,1:25:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you just leave?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.40,1:25:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I loved you girls.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.53,1:25:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted you to come with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.47,1:25:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- But you had to wait for the Blood Moon.\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.17,1:25:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By birthright...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.87,1:25:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the gift would go first\Nto my eldest daughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.54,1:25:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So I forged a letter.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.28,1:25:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But when I tried to speak to her...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.25,1:25:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Henry's not coming, Lucie.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.05,1:25:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- She didn't understand me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.39,1:25:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any offspring of mine with my wolf\Nblood would've been able to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.46,1:26:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then it all made sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.73,1:26:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucie couldn't be my daughter.\NYour mother lied to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.10,1:26:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you knew that already, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.04,1:26:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all these years of being so clever\Nand so careful, I just lost control.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.51,1:26:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for Lucie.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.78,1:26:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You took revenge on Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.85,1:26:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And her lover.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.82,1:26:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Henry smelled the wolf that night.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.26,1:26:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And then again yesterday.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.03,1:26:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He thought the smell{\i}\N{\i1}came from your grandmother.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.63,1:26:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But she had lived{\i}\N{\i1}with that smell her whole life.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.24,1:26:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You see, my father was a wolf too.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.94,1:26:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The smell remained on his clothing.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.68,1:26:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mother never knew what it meant...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.25,1:26:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...till the moment she died.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.49,1:27:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I loved her.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.70,1:27:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her and Lucie both.\NI never wanted to hurt them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.67,1:27:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valerie, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.14,1:27:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the last day of the Blood Moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.71,1:27:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One bite, and you'll be like me.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.48,1:27:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't do what you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.01,1:27:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.35,1:27:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you can, Valerie.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.08,1:27:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My blood already\Ncourses through your veins.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.19,1:27:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.29,1:27:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a gift my father gave to me\Nthat now I can give to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.93,1:27:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm stronger than he was,\Nyou'll be even stronger than me.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.67,1:27:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.13,1:27:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will be invincible.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.51,1:27:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There must be a God,\Nbecause you're the devil.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.18,1:27:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're the devil's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.75,1:28:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not so terrifying\Nwhen the sun is up.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.39,1:28:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How would you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.01,1:28:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.91,1:28:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have something for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.53,1:29:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.50,1:29:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get me out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.67,1:29:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.74,1:29:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He bit me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.52,1:29:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the moon rises...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.72,1:29:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll be like him.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.66,1:29:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A beast.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.77,1:30:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everything I knew was ripped apart.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.61,1:30:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I saw it all differently.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.98,1:30:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All the lies. My mother's, my father's.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.48,1:30:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He was all I had left.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.55,1:30:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.89,1:30:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even when I doubted him...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.06,1:30:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...even when I wounded him...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.96,1:30:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...Peter was true.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.51,1:30:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.37,1:32:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one can know about your father.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.51,1:32:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll hang you...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.44,1:32:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...for being the daughter of the wolf.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.84,1:33:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.55,1:33:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.81,1:33:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be safe with me...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.62,1:33:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...until I learn how to protect you from...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.03,1:34:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.73,1:34:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd say that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.09,1:34:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was the most brutal winter{\i}\N{\i1}I could remember.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.43,1:34:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Daggerhorn fell back{\i}\N{\i1}into its old rhythms.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.00,1:34:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wolf didn't come back.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.03,1:34:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But the village still lived in fear.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.58,1:34:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was the only life they knew.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.43,1:35:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Henry found his courage.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.76,1:35:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He chose a life of honor{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.03,1:35:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}protecting us from darkness.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.24,1:35:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With time, my mother realized that Father{\i}\N{\i1}would never return to Daggerhorn.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.64,1:35:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I could no longer live there...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.34,1:35:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...with my secret.{\i}

